com.wikitude.common.permission

Interface PermissionManager.PermissionManagerCallback

  • Enclosing interface:
    PermissionManager

    public static interface PermissionManager.PermissionManagerCallback
    Callbacks of the PermissionManager.
    It can be used to define what happens on the following events:
    • permissionsGranted(int requestCode)
    • permissionsDenied(String[])
    • showPermissionRationale(int, String[])

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void permissionsDenied(String[] deniedPermissions)
      One or more requested permissions were denied.
      void permissionsGranted(int requestCode)
      Requested permissions were granted.
      void showPermissionRationale(int requestCode, String[] permissions)
      User denied the permission request before, explain why the app needs the permissions.
      If the user wants to grant the permissions call PermissionManager.positiveRationaleResult(int, java.lang.String[]).

      • showPermissionRationale

        void showPermissionRationale(int requestCode,
                             String[] permissions)
        User denied the permission request before, explain why the app needs the permissions.
        If the user wants to grant the permissions call PermissionManager.positiveRationaleResult(int, java.lang.String[]).
        Parameters:
        requestCode - The permission request identifier passed in PermissionManager.checkPermissions(android.app.Activity, java.lang.String[], int, com.wikitude.common.permission.PermissionManager.PermissionManagerCallback).
        permissions - The array containing one or more Manifest.permission.
